The paper deals with the complexity of solving propositional satisfiability, which is a problem that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The analysis of the optimal choices in DPLL and resolution involves concepts from logic (cs.LO) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of determining the size of optimal proofs, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
